(13, 100, 'Editing_help', 'Editing help', 'You can use the following markup to enhance the look and functionality of pages:\n				\n## Links\n\n<Wiki:NoParse>\nTo create a link to another wiki page, simply use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page"/>`. To change the text of the link, use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page">Alternative Text</Wiki:Link>`.\n</Wiki:NoParse>\n\n## Formatting\n\nMost formatting can be done using either Markdown or pure HTML:\n\n### Headlines\n\nUse `#` to create headlines - the more `#` the smaller the text:\n\n```\n# One for a level 1 headline\n## Two for a level 2 headline\n### Three for a level 3 headline\n#### Three for a level 4 headline\n##### Three for a level 5 headline\n###### Three for a level 6 headline\n```\n\n### Italic text\n\nUse `*` to create italics:\n\n`This text has *italics*.`  \nThis text has *italics*.\n\n### Bold text\n\nUse `**` to create bold text:\n\n`This text has **bold letters.**`  \nThis text has **bold letters.**\n\n### Line breaks\n\nA blank line automatically creates a new paragraph. To add a manual linebreak within a paragraph, add two spaces (`  `) at the end of a line and continue writing at the next line:\n\n```\nThis is the first paragraph.\n\nThis is the second paragraph.\nThis still belongs to the second paragraph and will be on the same line.\n\nThis is the third paragraph, and there are two spaces right here:  \nThis still belongs to the third paragraph and will be on a new line.\n```\n\nThis is the first paragraph.\n\nThis is the second paragraph.\nThis still belongs to the second paragraph and will be on the same line.\n\nThis is the third paragraph, and there are two spaces right here:  \nThis still belongs to the third paragraph and will be on a new line.\n\n### Deactivate page renderer\n\nYou can temporarily deactivate the page renderer with <Wiki:NoParse>`<Wiki:NoParse>Text that will not be touched</Wiki;NoParse>`</Wiki:NoParse>. However, this only deactivates the page renderer, not the Markdown converter.\n\n## Bootstrap components\n\nThe following options use components of the Twitter Bootstrap framework.\n\n### Icons\n\n<Wiki:NoParse>`<Wiki:Icon name="plus"/>`</Wiki:NoParse>\n<Wiki:Label theme="default"><Wiki:Icon name="plus"/> A plus icon on a label</Wiki:Label>\n\n### Panels\n\n## Presentation mode\n				\nIn **presentation mode** the focus is all on the content of your page. You can disable the navigation bar with <Wiki:NoParse>`<Wiki:NoNavbar/>`</Wiki:NoParse> and the headline (plus the separator below) with <Wiki:NoParse>`<Wiki:NoHeadline/>`</Wiki:NoParse>.\n\n<Wiki:Panel theme="warning" title="Tip">Deactivating the navigation bar also removes the link to the page editor. To edit a page you need to append `#Edit` to the URL in the address bar: `http://wiki.domain.com/My_Page.html#Edit`.</Wiki:Panel>\n\n## Scripting\n\nIt is also possible to use PHP code inside a page. Simply wrap your script inside `<?php` (`<?` does not work here!) and `?>`.\n\n<Wiki:Panel theme="danger" title="Warning">If a single script block is found inside a page the renderer will remodel the whole page to be wrapped as a script. This means that the code you see in the composer is not necessarily the same code that will be executed!</Wiki:Panel>\n\nFor example, the following script:\n\n<Wiki:NoParse>\n```\nThis is a page with a "script" inside. <?php $text = "Hello world!"; ?> Regular text continues here. <?php echo $text; %>\n```\n</Wiki:NoParse>\n\nwill be converted to:\n\n<Wiki:NoParse>\n```\n<?php echo "This is a page with a \\"script\\" inside."; $text = "Hello world!"; echo "Regular text continues here."; echo $text; ?>\n```\n</Wiki:NoParse>\n\nThis does not change the output of the content - both scripts print `This is a page with a "script" inside. Regular text continues here. Hello world!`.', 1, 'PUBLIC');
