(41, 100, 13, 'Editing help', 'You can use the following markup to enhance the look and functionality of pages:\n				\n## Links\n\n## Presentation mode\n				\nIn **presentation mode** the focus is all on the content of your page. You can disable the navigation bar with `<Wiki:NoParse><Wiki:NoNavbar/></Wiki:NoParse>` and the headline (plus the separator below) with `<Wiki:NoParse><Wiki:NoHeadline></Wiki:NoParse>`.\n\n<Wiki:Panel theme="warning" title="Tip">Deactivating the navigation bar also removes the link to the page editor. To edit a page you need to append `#Edit` to the URL in the address bar: `http://wiki.domain.com/My_Page.html**#Edit**`.</Wiki:Panel>', '', b'0'),
(42, 100, 13, 'Editing help', '<Wiki:NoParse>\n\nYou can use the following markup to enhance the look and functionality of pages:\n				\n## Links\n\nTo create a link to another wiki page, simply use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page"/>`. To change the text of the link, use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page">Alternative Text</Wiki:Link>`.\n\n## Presentation mode\n				\nIn **presentation mode** the focus is all on the content of your page. You can disable the navigation bar with `<Wiki:NoNavbar/>` and the headline (plus the separator below) with `<Wiki:NoHeadline>`.\n\n</Wiki:NoParse>\n\n<Wiki:Panel theme="warning" title="Tip">Deactivating the navigation bar also removes the link to the page editor. To edit a page you need to append `#Edit` to the URL in the address bar: `http://wiki.domain.com/My_Page.html**#Edit**`.</Wiki:Panel>', '', b'0'),
(43, 100, 13, 'Editing help', '<Wiki:NoParse>\n\nYou can use the following markup to enhance the look and functionality of pages:\n				\n## Links\n\nTo create a link to another wiki page, simply use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page"/>`. To change the text of the link, use `<Wiki:Link page="Name_of_the_target_page">Alternative Text</Wiki:Link>`.\n\n## Formatting\n\nUse `#` to create headlines:\n\n# One for a level 1 headline (`#`)\n## Two for a level 2 headline (`##`)\n### Three for a level 3 headline (`###`)\n\n## Presentation mode\n				\nIn **presentation mode** the focus is all on the content of your page. You can disable the navigation bar with `<Wiki:NoNavbar/>` and the headline (plus the separator below) with `<Wiki:NoHeadline>`.\n\n</Wiki:NoParse>\n\n<Wiki:Panel theme="warning" title="Tip">Deactivating the navigation bar also removes the link to the page editor. To edit a page you need to append `#Edit` to the URL in the address bar: `http://wiki.domain.com/My_Page.html**#Edit** `.</Wiki:Panel>', '', b'0'),
